        "timestamp": "2021-06-21 15:50:42.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n(1 comment)\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> how does it work for unit testing handled adding new camel endpoints?\n\nthere should be a way to junit test a camel route",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "23418b2ae90fdc98b002843320b61f2004a42a1e",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 7660,
          "name": "Bruno Militzer",
          "display_name": "Bruno Militzer",
          "email": "bruno.militzer@est.tech",
          "username": "brunomilitzer"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2021-06-22 08:36:35.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nHello Seb, how do you implement the Camel Rest Endpoint Unit Tests, I couldn't find in the code.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "2c6772fb9931b1c439741659fb7fb26eb7d96c3b",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 23,
          "name": "S�bastien Determe",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "sebastien.determe@intl.att.com",
          "username": "sebdet"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2021-06-22 13:32:47.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nHi Bruno,\n\nSearch for the DeployFlowTestItCase, in that class you have multiple examples to Camel routes.\nThose are part of the maven integration tests as they require Mariadb, emulator docker images running.\n\nWe always tried to avoid mocking as it's generally a loss of time and resources, better to automate tests with real compo mainly when the tests can be developed in Junit 😊",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "dfe37f1b484206644e0988ee388583cc36fbac2a",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 23,
          "name": "S�bastien Determe",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "sebastien.determe@intl.att.com",
          "username": "sebdet"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2021-06-22 13:37:41.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nBruno, please note that you have also an additional option if you want to test your rest interface directly (the best being to have 2 levels of testing of course but that's not mandatory).\n\nSearch for RobotItCase, during the maven integration test phase, we execute Robot Framework tests in a docker container (it has been introduced recently). You can add your Robot tests in the folder .../test/resources/robotframework/tests.\n\nPlease note that by calling Camel direclty or by executing robot framework tests, the coverage will be recorded.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "224c7de20b4ffb16d76066b6ee2d3019afb91c49",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 7660,
          "name": "Bruno Militzer",
          "display_name": "Bruno Militzer",
          "email": "bruno.militzer@est.tech",
          "username": "brunomilitzer"
        },
        "author_role": "CI_BOT",
        "timestamp": "2021-06-22 14:46:10.000000000",
        "message": "Uploaded patch set 2.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "8dc7a3b02846667a03a2d69de690dcf69273f74d",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 7660,
          "name": "Bruno Militzer",
          "display_name": "Bruno Militzer",
          "email": "bruno.militzer@est.tech",
          "username": "brunomilitzer"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2021-06-22 14:48:16.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> Bruno, please note that you have also an additional option if you want to test your rest interface directly (the best being to have 2 levels of testing of course but that's not mandatory).\n> \n> Search for RobotItCase, during the maven integration test phase, we execute Robot Framework tests in a docker container (it has been introduced recently). You can add your Robot tests in the folder .../test/resources/robotframework/tests.\n> \n> Please note that by calling Camel direclty or by executing robot framework tests, the coverage will be recorded.\n\nWe are planning to have a Sprint meeting today and we are thinking in opening up a separate Jira to create these tests.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
